President Muhammadu Buhari on Tuesday felicitated with Deacon Samson Maliki Dikki, foremost Quantity Surveyor who contributed greatly to the physical development of Sokoto and Kebbi states, as he turned 70.
The Special Adviser to the President, Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, in a statement indicated that President Buhari rejoiced with the family, friends and associates of the man who impacted greatly on the two states in the areas of Architecture and Building, while in the civil service, wishing him length of days and good health.
According to the statement: “President Buhari commends the Deacon from Zulu Local Government Area of Kebbi State for adroitly combining service to God with service to humanity, both at community and State levels, and recommends such devotion to the younger generation.
“The President also congratulates all those rejoicing with Deacon Dikki at this auspicious occasion.”
 
